  "description": [
    "Page 4 _______ TOLEDO UNION JOURNAL 1MTED II1 ST AM Published every Fridav by Local No 13 UAVVCiO 425 Winthrop Street Toledo Ohio Member of American Labor Press Association Editor Melvin Schultz a nagin Editor O J Pecord Advertising Manager Burny Zawodny Board of Trustees Melvin Schultz Thomas Burke Randolph Gray SUBSCRIPTION RATES One vcar bv mail in advance Entered at the Toledo Ohio post office as second class matter under the act of Aug 24 1912 Stiffer Manpower Control Labor leaders are apprehensive of War Mobilization Director James F Byrne directive promulgated August 10 which gives the most drastic control over man power since the war began Despite the reassuring words War Manpower Commission heads the power placed in the hands of the area manpower directors could be used arbitrarily to han dicap labor Under the terms of the new controls workers can be forced out of less essential plants into those designated as critical Moreover workers so referred for work in critical industries may be terminated fired if they refuse suitable employment without good cause Union leaders have serious doubts that such drastic controls are needed at all now that the war is progressing so satisfac torily They"
